# Neon MCP Server Usage

The Neon MCP server (`user-Neon`) connects directly to the Neon project.
Use it instead of writing scripts or SQL files whenever possible.

## When to Use Neon MCP

| Task | Use Neon MCP tool | NOT this |
|------|-------------------|----------|
| Schema change (add table/column) | `prepare_database_migration` → `complete_database_migration` | Writing migration .js files |
| Inspect tables / columns | `get_database_tables`, `describe_table_schema` | Reading schema.sql |
| One-off SQL query | `run_sql` | Writing a temp script |
| Debug slow queries | `list_slow_queries`, `explain_sql_statement` | Manual EXPLAIN |
| Enable Data API on a branch | `provision_neon_data_api` | Clicking in Neon Console |

## Key Tools

- **`run_sql`** – Execute any SQL against the `neondb` database
- **`prepare_database_migration`** – Creates a safe temp branch, applies schema change, tests it
- **`complete_database_migration`** – Merges tested migration to main branch
- **`get_database_tables`** / **`describe_table_schema`** – Inspect live schema
- **`list_slow_queries`** – Find performance bottlenecks (needs `pg_stat_statements`)
- **`provision_neon_data_api`** – Enable Data API programmatically

## Migration Workflow (ALWAYS use branching)

```
prepare_database_migration  →  test SQL on temp branch  →  complete_database_migration
```
Never apply schema changes directly with `run_sql` to the main branch.

## Project Details

- Project ID: `rapid-wildflower-52568597`
- Main database: `neondb`
- Branch: `main`

## App Data Access Pattern

Neon MCP = developer tooling (schema, admin queries)
`src/lib/dataClient.js` = runtime app queries (Data API + RLS)

Never use MCP tools in application code. MCP is for dev/admin tasks only.
